author: Erin Gallagher
title: Man dies after being ejected from SUV in Will County Daily Southtown
text:
A man was found dead in a Will County cornfield Friday morning after he apparently was ejected from his SUV when it rolled off a road, police said.
The man, who has not been identified, was discovered about 6:30 a.m. near a red Ford SUV along Pauling Road near Barten Road in unincorporated Manhattan Township, according to Will County Sheriff Sgt. Vince Gambino. The coroner arrived on the scene about 9 a.m.
Gambino said it appeared to be a single-vehicle incident. Official did not know what time the incident occurred. The man's family was being notified.
Pauling Road at that location is a gravel road with soft shoulders.
Check back for more details.
Erin Gallagher is a freelance reporter.
